cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method for anomaly detection in natural image datasets using deep generative models (DGMs) leveraging deep neural networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.MM (Multimedia). The focus on image datasets and deep neural networks makes cs.CV the most likely category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of probabilistic models and regularization terms also suggests a potential fit with cs.NE and cs.MM.
